						<div class="postbody">Disclaimer: I too am a Super NES noob although with NES experience.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You really should turn on NMI when VBlank fires, otherwise your <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">wai</tt> in WaitVBL doesn't serve a purpose.</div><br />True. But isn't it a good idea to disable NMI during the init code and reenable it afterward to make sure the NMI handler doesn't mess things up?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">you could replace that whole thing with just wai ; rts and be done with it</div><br />Possibly, although with other things turned on, it might just end up waiting for the scanline number to equal VTIMEL ($4209).</div>

