						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You really should turn on NMI when VBlank fires, otherwise your <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">wai</tt> in WaitVBL doesn't serve a purpose.</div><br />True. But isn't it a good idea to disable NMI during the init code and reenable it afterward to make sure the NMI handler doesn't mess things up?</div><br />Yes, which is why it should be enabled prior to the rest of his routines, which is what my statement was implying.  I'm seriously not going to sit around writing code for people.  :P</div>

