					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">&gt; if $00-$3F and $80-$BF are bank addresses, does that mean that there are actually 128 banks on which the MSU1 registers are mirrored? That sounds quite a lot to me<br /><br />Yes, that's how the SNES works. Same deal for all your regular registers, $2100 and such. It's a problem when DBR.d6 is set, eg: lda #$40; pha; plb; stz $2100 &lt;- does not write to display register, as $402100 is not an MMIO region, it's a CART (ROM) address.<br /><br />&gt; Also, if $002002-$002008 is a correct address for reading the MSU1 presence identificator, I must be doing something terribly wrong because I couldn't read these bytes correctly to save my life.<br /><br />With higan v094, you need a manifest.bml file to specify that the MSU1 is present. With sd2snes, you need a gamename.msu file to specify that it's present.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

